name: 5PPEH
description: By striking the five vital points, the Miyako priests teach advanced tamers how to doom and immunize a target for 5 turns.
effectText: 5PPEH inflicts a single other target with a 5 turn countdown of the Doomed Condition but also gifts them with the Immune Condition for 5 turns.

name: Acid Reflux
description: Toxolotl draws from the Toxic essence of Xolot, moderately damaging and Poisoning the whole team for 2 turns.
effectText: Acid Reflux deals damage to the rival team or the user's ally and inflicts them with the Poisoned Condition for 2 turns.

name: Allergic Spread
description: A burst of allergen spores that inflicts damage on the whole team.
effectText: Allergic Spread deals damage to the rival team or the user's ally.

name: Ampere Outburst
description: Volgon's Heavenly Might unleashes a wave of power that strikes the entire team. When using this technique, both Volgon and his ally get their Hold decreased by 1.
effectText: Ampere Outburst deals damage to the other team or the user's ally and reduces the Hold of techniques by 1 for itself and its ally.

name: Antitoxins
description: Advanced antitoxins that cure poison on the inoculated target and invigorate them for 2 turns.
effectText: Antitoxins cures a single team of the Poisoned Condition and gifts them with the Invigorated Condition for 2 turns if they were Poisoned.

name: Aqua Bullet Hell
description: A devastating Water technique developed by legendary tamer Dan Maku.
effectText: Aqua Bullet Hell deals damage to a single other target.

name: Aqua Stone
description: "An ingenious application of hydraulic pressure for ballistic purposes" - Sophia d'Arissola.
effectText: Aqua Stone deals damage to a single other target.
synergyText: If used with an Earth ally, its damage increases to 135.

name: Aquatic Whirlwind
description: This Water technique is faster than an angry Kalabyss.
effectText: Aquatic Whirlwind deals damage to a single target.

name: Autodestruction
description: Let's press the big red button with the danger signs! The Digital attacker inflicts massive damage and self-destructs in the process.
effectText: Autodestruction's damage formula is close, but not exactly equal to, the combination of the damage it would deal based on ATK and the damage it would deal based on DEF. The exact formula is intended to be:

name: Awful Song
description: Ninety-nine Temesseeeence viaaaals! This horrible Tucmani drinking song does considerable damage... especially to reputations, inflicting isolation for 3 turns.Used in combination with a Neutral ally, the Awful Song inflicts damage on the whole team.
effectText: Awful Song deals damage to a single target and inflicts them with the Isolated Condition for 3 turns.
synergyText: If used with a Neutral ally, its targeting changes Other Team or Ally. As such, if the user targets themselves and the synergy activates, only the user's ally will be damaged.

name: Bamboozle
description: Give'em the old razzle dazzle! The target evades for 2 turns. This technique starts with 0 Hold.
effectText: Bamboozle gifts a single target with the Evading Condition for 2 turns. After using this technique for the first time in battle, it will have hold 1 for the rest of the match.

name: Bark
description: This Tem's bark is much worse than its bite - it gives the enemy DEF and SPDEF .
effectText: Bark inflicts a single other target with DEF and SPDEF .

name: Bark Shield
description: Omninenesian Temtem use pieces of Banyan bark as shields, giving the whole team DEF .
effectText: Bark Shield gifts a single team with DEF .

name: Base Jump
description: It's not the jump that hurts, it's the landing - and it hurts the target A LOT.
effectText: Base Jump deals damage to a single other target.

name: Beef Up
description: This reinforcing technique grants ATK to the target. Eat your proteins, Tamers!.
effectText: Beef Up gifts a single target with ATK .

name: Bestial Charge
description: A primal charge, like the stampede on the Kisiwa plains! It inflicts damage on the whole team.
effectText: Bestial Charge deals damage to the rival team or the user's ally.

name: Hypoxia
description: Watch your enemies choke as you turn around and... take their breath away.
effectText: Hypoxia deals damage to a single target.

name: Ice Cubes
description: An extreme version of the ice water bucket challenge that does real damage.Used in combination with a Wind ally, produces Cold for 1 turn.
effectText: Ice Cubes deals damage to a single other target.
synergyText: If used with a Wind ally, its STA Cost decreases to 9, Damage increases to 70, and Priority changes to Very High while inflicting them with the Cold Condition for 1 turn.

name: Ice Shuriken
description: An obscure technique created by the secretive Iwaba clan, deep in the Cipanki hills, which inflicts Cold for 2 turns.
effectText: Ice Shuriken deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with the Cold Condition for 2 turns.

name: Iced Stalactite
description: Cold *does* bother you anyway... This giant icicle inflicts damage and also Cold for 2 turns.
effectText: Iced Stalactite deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with the Cold Condition for 2 turns.

name: Inner Spirit
description: It is said this technique channels the spirit of a long-lost, draconic variety of Temtem, for massive damage.
effectText: Inner Spirit deals damage to a single target.

name: Intimidation
description: That "don't mess with me" look makes the target team exhausted for 2 turns. Also grants the user evading for 1 turn.
effectText: Intimidation inflicts the rival team or the user's ally with the Exhausted Condition for 2 turns and gifts the user with the Evading Condition for 1 turn.

name: Jaw Strike
description: Temtem with powerful jaws always know how to use them...
effectText: Jaw Strike deals damage to a single other target.

name: Jinxed Whisper
description: Shh! Shut up, you're jinxing your chances! The target falls asleep for 2 turns, but the user gets overextended on the next turn.
effectText: Jinxed Whisper inflicts a single other target with the Asleep Condition for 1 turns but causes the user to be overexerted the next turn.

name: King's Roar
description: When the king roars, the rest run away. Decreases SPD , ATK and SPATK of the other team.
effectText: King's Roar inflicts the rival team or the user's ally with SPD , ATK and SPATK .

name: Knockback
description: What goes around comes around! This mighty attack inflicts massive damage, but the user gets 30% knockback damage.
effectText: Knockback deals damage to a single other target but causes the user to take 30% of the damage dealt as recoil.

name: Late Torment
description: The first cut is the deepest, but the last one hurts like Downbelow. This Neutral Technique only works on trapped enemies and inflicts 180 damage.
effectText: Late Torment deals damage to a single other target if they're afflicted with the Trapped Condition.

name: Laundry

synergyEffects.effect: Removes positive Stat Stage changes from the target.

description: Look, nobody likes doing laundry, but it has to be done, OK? It cleans all statuses, naturally! (And does some damage to boot.).Used in combination with an ally, Laundry washes away all positive stage modifications on rivals.
effectText: Laundry deals damage to a single target and cures/removes all of their Status Conditions.
synergyText: If used with an Electric ally, its priority increases to High and removes positive Stat Stage changes from the target.

name: Lava Wave
description: Some Temtem like a hot batch, and some like it PIPING hot. This technique inflicts moderate damage.Love me a streamin' bath! Used in combination with a Water ally, Lava Wave seizes for 3 turns and increases priority.
effectText: Lava Wave deals damage to a single other target.
synergyText: If used with a Water ally, its priority increases to High and inflicts the Seized Condition for 3 turns.

name: Leech
description: Normally Taifu prefer cookies... but if there's nothing else available, they'll strike and heal themselves 45% of the damage dealt.When paired with a Water Temtem, Taifu strike harder and heal themselves for 55% of the damage dealt.
effectText: Leech damages a single other target and restores 45% of the damage dealt to the user.
synergyText: If used with a Water ally, its priority increases to High and the user is healed for 55% of the damage dealt.

name: Lifeful Sap
description: The sap of life, from the living heart of the Giant Banyan. Heals 10% HP for 5 turns.
effectText: Lifeful Sap gifts the user with the Regenerated Condition for 5 turns.

name: Look out
description: This Temtem has (metaphorical) eyes on the back of its head. This hyperalert state makes it alerted for 2 turns and removes the Asleep status condition.
effectText: Look out gifts the team with the Alerted Condition for 2 turns and cures them of the Asleep Condition. Unlike other techniques, it will set the duration of any previously gifted Alerted Conditions to 2 turns.

name: Lullaby
description: Twinkle twinkle little Tem / Whole opponent team falls Asleep for 2 turns.
effectText: Lullaby inflicts the rival team or the user's ally with the Asleep Condition for 2 turns.

name: Madness Buff
description: There is an edge to this madness - those willing to take 25% Damage will get SPDEF and SPATK .
effectText: Madness Buff causes the user to lose 25% of their maximum HP and then is gifted SPATK and SPDEF .

name: Magma Cannon
description: Like a surge of Anak lava to the face! Fire technique that burns for 2 turns.
effectText: Magma Cannon deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with the Burned Condition for 2 turns.

name: Major Slash
description: This blow targets the enemy's weak spot for massive damage.
effectText: Major Slash deals damage to a single other target.

name: Martial Strike
description: Many Melee Temtem are trained to perform this basic but effective technique.
effectText: Martial Strike deals damage to a single other target and grants the user SPATK .

name: Matter Teleport
description: Feels like being disintegrated into molecules - not nice. This Mental technique inflicts heavy damage.
effectText: Matter Teleport deals damage to a single target.

name: Mechanical Heat
description: Every moving part generates residual heat - and this is a way to weaponize it and inflict moderate damage.
effectText: Mechanical Heat deals damage to a single other target.

name: Nightmare Feed
description: Nothing creepier than feeding on a sleeping victim... Inflicts 30% damage to a sleeping enemy and heals the user by 30%.
effectText: Nightmare Feed causes a single target to lose 30% of their maximum HP and the user to restore 30% of their maximum HP if the target is afflicted with the Asleep Condition. It will not cause the target to wake up.

name: Nimble
description: Through rigorous training, Temtem can become extra fast and gain SPD .
effectText: Nimble gifts a single other target with SPD .

name: Ninja Jutsu
description: The secret arts of the Cipanku shinobi! This technique lets you backstab enemies in the blink of an eye.
effectText: Ninja Jutsu deals damage to a single other target.

name: Nito Seiho
description: Derived from Cipanki martial traditions, this technique deals a powerful Melee strike and gives them DEF .
effectText: Nito Seiho deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with DEF .

name: Novice Punch
description: Just one step above a slap, but everybody's got to start somewhere.Used in combination with a Melee ally, it changes the technique type to Melee and becomes a more powerful punch.
effectText: Novice Punch deals damage to a single other target.
synergyText: If used with a Melee ally, it becomes Melee Type and its damage increases to 51.

name: Noxious Bomb
description: This nasty stinker inflicts Toxic damage... Just don't use it in an elevator...
effectText: Noxious Bomb deals damage to a single target.

name: Oshi-Dashi
description: Going for the ring out can be a dangerous Melee move in the smallest islands...
effectText: Oshi-Dashi deals damage to a single other target.

name: Outgrowth
description: Behold Tyranak's complete mastery over everything that grows and thrives in their realm! Damages the whole enemy team, decreases their Stamina by 20%, and traps them for 2 turns.
effectText: Outgrowth deals damage to the rival team or the user's ally, causes them to lose 20% of their maximum STA, and inflicts them with the Trapped Condition for 2 turns.

name: Overclock
description: Unrecommended for longer periods, this technique makes your 'Tems go way faster, bestowing SPD .
effectText: Overclock gifts the user with SPD .

name: Peck
description: All beaked Temtems like to playfully peck their tamers. This is the less friendly version.
effectText: Peck deals damage to a single other target.

name: Penance
description: Blood magic requires blood sacrifice - will you pay the price? Loatle can inflict 100% of damage on itself to boost the ATK and SPATK of the target.
effectText: Penance gifts a single other target with ATK and SPATK but causes the user to lose 100% of their maximum HP.

name: Perfect Jab
description: Strike smarter, not harder. Weak, but enemy get DEF .
effectText: Perfect Jab deals damage to a single target and inflicts them with DEF .

name: Petal Dagger
description: Even the most harmless flowers have their weapons. Kill them all with softness!
effectText: Petal Dagger deals damage to a single other target.

name: Petrify
description: Have a heart... of stone. It doesn't hurt much, but it leaves enemies trapped for 2 turns, and overexerts them next turn.
effectText: Petrify deals damage to a single target, inflicts Trapped Condition for 2 turns, and leaves the target overexerted next turn.

name: Phantom Whiplash
description: There are unseen forces at play here. Hits fast, hits hard, and you'll remember it for days.
effectText: Phantom Whiplash deals damage to a single other target.

name: Rush
description: Hard or weak, what really matters is striking first. This superfast technique does exactly 40 damage but overextends the user for the next turn.
effectText: Rush deals an exact 40 damage to a single other target regardless of DEF, SPDEF, Type Effectivness, or Traits, but causes the user to be overexerted the next turn.

name: Sacrifice
description: A Temtem may pay the ultimate price to heal the target of all Status conditions and give them DEF and SPDEF .
effectText: Sacrifice removes/cures a single other target of all Status Conditions and gifts them with DEF and SPDEF , then the user is knocked-out.

name: Sanative Rain

synergyEffects.effect: Restore 20% of allies maximum HP Restore 10% of rival's maximum HP

description: Known as "the blessing rains of Kisiwa", this shamanic technique heals 15% of every Temtem on the battlefield..Used in combination with a Wind ally, Sanative Rain heals allied Temtem by 20% but enemies by only 10%.
effectText: Sanative Rain restores 15% of all combatants on the battlefield's maximum HP.
synergyText: If used with a Wind ally, its priority increases to Normal and instead restores 20% of allies' maximum HP and restores 10% of rivals' maximum HP.

name: Sand Splatter
description: A fistful of humble sand becomes a face full of dirty fighting.
effectText: Sand Splatter deals damage to a single other target.

name: Sand Storm
description: Developed by the legendary tamer Da-Rud in ancient times, this Earth technique inflicts decent damage & Isolation on the whole team.
effectText: Sand Storm deals damage & Isolation for 2 turns to the whole team.

name: Scratch
description: Almost any claw or nail can scratch the surface. Sometimes that's enough.
effectText: Scratch deals damage to a single other target.

name: Selfless Ruination
description: Doom counter is lowered by two turns, but it applies DEF , SPDEF and one turn of evasion to the target.
effectText: Selfless Ruination reduces the amount of Doomed turns of the user by two, while also giving the selected target of Selfless Ruination DEF , SPDEF and one turn of Evading.

name: Sharp Leaf
description: Evolution has armed Nature Temtem with advanced defenses against herbivores.
effectText: Sharp Leaf deals damage to a single other target.

name: Sharp Rain
description: Rather like snow, if snow was razor-sharp ice needles instead of gentle flakes.
effectText: Sharp Rain deals damage to a single target.

name: Sharp Stabs
description: Like winter in the Kilima peaks, this blizzard of sharp shards is as fast as piercing.
effectText: Sharp Stabs deals damage to a single other target.

name: Sharpening
description: Sharpen those claws, it's time to tear through the opposition! This technique bestows increased ATK and SPD .
effectText: Sharpening gifts the user with SPD and ATK .

name: Time Split
description: Twist the fabric of time-space to your advantage, gaining SPD and giving the enemy SPD .
effectText: Time Split deals damage to a single other target then gifts the user with SPD and inflicts the target with SPD .

name: Token
description: Launch token attacks, get token results. This technique does little damage and exiles the target for 1 turn.
effectText: Token deals damage to a single target and inflicts them with the Isolated Condition for 1 turn.

name: Tornado
description: A powerful wind technique, illegal to use near all airship terminals of the Archipelago.
effectText: Tornado deals damage to a single target.

name: Tortenite's Garden

synergyEffects.effect: Restore 20% of user's maximum HP 3 Turns  Doomed

description: Lil' Tort just wanted to play in its garden... but it won't suffer intruders! You heal 10% while the target is Doomed for 4 turns.Used in combination with a Crystal ally, Tortenite's Garden heals 20% and inflicts Doomed for 3 turns instead of 4.
effectText: Tortenite's Garden inflicts a single other target with a 4 turn countdown of the Doomed Condition and restores 10% of the user's maximum HP.
synergyText: If used with a Crystal ally, the Doomed Condition has a 3 turn countdown and restores 20% of the user's maximum HP.

name: Toxic Spores
description: Toxin-carrying spores that inoculate with Poisoned for 3 turns.
effectText: Toxic Spores inflicts a single other target with the Poisoned Condition for 3 turns.

name: Toxic Torrent
description: "Chromeon, show me your Toxic side!" This technique inflicts moderate damage.
effectText: Toxic Torrent deals damage to a single other target.

name: Toxin Shower
description: Soak everyone in nasty toxins - but don't splash yourself! Inflicts moderate damage on everyone but you, and lets you evade for 1 turn.
effectText: Toxin Shower deals damage to all other combatants on the battlefield and gifts the user with the Evading Condition for turn.

name: Trample
effectText: Trample inflicts damage to the rival team or the user's ally. If this technique knocks an opponent out, the user gets ATK and SPATK .
synergyText: If used with a Melee ally, it changes from a Special to a Physical technique.

name: Transient Echo
description: There and back again! This technique deals medium damage and gives -1 Hold.
effectText: Transient Echo deals damage to a single other target and gifts the user -1 Hold to all Techniques.

name: Tsunami
description: Summon a rarely seen tidal wave that damages a whole team.Uses in combination with a Wind ally, damage boost and Cold for 1 Turn.
effectText: Tsunami deals damage to the rival team or the user's ally.
synergyText: If used with a Wind ally, its damage increases to 80 and also inflicts the Cold Condition for 1 turn.

name: Turbine
description: Swift as the wind and as harsh and razor sharp as a wintery gale. This technique is fast and inflicts decent damage.
effectText: Turbine deals damage to a single other target.

name: Turbo Attack
description: Time to supercharge your attack - like nitro, but for Temtem!
effectText: Turbo Attack deals damage to a single target.

name: Unseen Blow
description: Nothing hurts like the blow you didn't see coming! This technique inflicts heavy damage.
effectText: Unseen Blow deals damage to a single other target.

name: Untangle
description: With a few swift movement, this techniques Untraps the target from any tangle. If trapped is removed successfully, the target gets DEF and SPDEF .
effectText: Untangle cures a single target of the Trapped Condition and gifts them with DEF and SPDEF if they were cured from the Trapped Condition.

name: Uppercut
description: Melee Temtem are all about raw strength. This technique is its sincerest expression.
effectText: Uppercut deals damage to a single other target.

name: Urushiol
description: The substance known as Urushiol is a virulent toxic agent.Urushiol's synergy with a Toxic ally Poisons the enemy for 4 turns.
effectText: Urushiol deals damage to a single other target.
synergyText: If used with a Toxic ally, it also inflicts the Poisoned Condition for 4 turns.

name: Venom Spread
description: This technique only works on already poisoned enemies - but in that case, the toxin rush inflicts 150 damage.
effectText: Venom Spread deals damage to a single target if they're afflicted with the Poisoned Condition.

name: Water Cannon
description: The strongest Sillaro current has nothing on this unstoppable jet.Used in combination with a Toxic ally, it produces a stream of Poison for 2 turns.
effectText: Water Cannon deals damage to a single other target.
synergyText: If used with a Toxic ally, it also inflicts the Poisoned Condition for 2 turns.

name: Water Cutting Lily
description: As pretty than Denizan Water lilies... but much deadlier.
effectText: Water Cutting Lily deals damage to a single target.
synergyText: If used with a Water ally, its damage increases to 134 and priority increases to High.

name: Water Stream
description: Like many Water Temtem, Koish can use jets of water to inflict moderate damage.
effectText: Water Stream deals damage to a single target.

name: Water Torrent
description: "Chromeon, it's time to hose 'em down!" This technique inflicts moderate damage.
effectText: Water Torrent deals damage to a single other target.
